  "text": "In view of this, Nelson (264) has proposed that activation of Cl Ϫ channels may explain stretch-induced depolarization of VSM. Support for this idea derives from the observation that Cl Ϫ channel inhibitors (DIDS and indanyloxyacetic acid) hyperpolarize rat cerebral artery myocytes and inhibit myogenic tone of pressurized cerebral arteries [CITATION_1] . In addition, reduction of [Cl Ϫ ] o from ϳ120 to 60 mM (which shifts the calculated E Cl to Ϫ2 mV) enhances pressure-induced myogenic tone in cerebral arteries.",
