      "span_text": "In view of this, Nelson (264) has proposed that activation of Cl Ϫ channels may explain stretch-induced depolarization of VSM. Support for this idea derives from the observation that Cl Ϫ channel inhibitors (DIDS and indanyloxyacetic acid) hyperpolarize rat cerebral artery myocytes and inhibit myogenic tone of pressurized cerebral arteries  ."
